				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				   Hello everyone. I would just like to say that i havent played EQ in a while now. Its been about 6 months. And while the convultions, and nerve pains have stopped. I still have that desire to do lame s*** like go fishing on a dock, make sets of banded for newbies, and other EQ pleasures. I can say that for the most part i had a great time playing EQ. I spend long hours and sometimes forgot to sleep. However, i also am reminded of people bickering with each other. Fights over guild power, players arguing over camps, problems with bugs, problems with the computer, problems with the connection, problems with GM's even. And all in all. I look back and the most memorable thing with EQ for me.. Was the name nazi Aberlin pulling me from the middle of a minor raid, ordering me to pick a new name while my group got slaughtered from my not being there to heal them. <BR>
<BR>
And... i think to my self... wow. I played that game for 2 years straight. and acumulated MONTHS of actual REAL-LIFE in game time. Thats like taking a 2 month vacation... into a fantasy world. While im glad i dont play anymore, im do have to say its an experiance ill never forget. <BR>
<BR>
 ---PREXUS---<BR>
Incogneto Otengocni<BR>
