				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Oh my God, people. You act as if this SMALL price increase is the end of the world. So what if you have to work another 24 hours a year. That's probably, what, another 3... 4 working days? Verant is not trying to rob you of your money, they need the money to keep up the maintenance of the game and work on future projects (the island chain or the mysterious continent we all saw on the screenshots of the globe) as Wilweyen Windrider said. I also agree that there are some things that Verant could improve to make the game better, but one step at a time.<BR>
I also agree with Freem in the fact that this IS like the rise in gas prices. Some may not be able to afford the prices, so you'll have to walk.<BR>
Also, I agree with Treeland. It's not Georgia's fault Verant rose the prices, so you don't need to be sending mail complaining about it.<BR>
Finally, I'd just like to say, being one of the unemployed, younger GamerFolk, I know that some of the kids out there won't be able to convince their parents to pay the higher prices (though it isn't really that much) and my deepest sympathy goes out to them (I, too, went through the first 7 months of simply owning the game and not being able to install it and play it because my parents refused to pay the $10).<BR>
